parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the push-to-start button can prevent the vehicle from starting, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The push-to-start button is inoperable
no warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the keyless start system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potentially safety risks.
symptoms: Error messages appear on the dashboard
such as "Vehicle key missing" or "Vehicle key not available or malfunctioning"
despite the key being present.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Cross Traffic Warning System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear cross traffic warning system can increase the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: The system fails to provide audible or visual warnings when traffic is crossing behind the vehicle
even when the vehicle is in reverse and close to an object.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The glitches in the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The navigation display and instrument panel black out intermittently
then restart
occurring during highway and city driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issues with the telematics system can cause inconvenience and potentially safety risks.
symptoms: Error messages appear on the dashboard
and the system may malfunction
causing anxiety and stress for the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated fogging of the front headlight enclosure due to moisture ingress can significantly reduce visibility, posing a safety risk to the driver and other road users.
symptoms: The front headlight enclosure fogs up
reducing visibility
especially at night or in low-light conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Auto-Dimming Feature in Digital Instrument Panel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poorly implemented auto-dimming feature in the digital instrument panel can cause the display to become extremely difficult to read, leading to unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The digital instrument panel dims inappropriately under variable lighting conditions
such as cloudy
snowy
sunrise
or sunset
making it difficult to read; the display is overly dimmed during daytime driving when headlights are not turned on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Sensor Malfunction due to Cup Holder Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty design of the cup holders, which allows liquid to leak onto the airbag sensors, can cause the airbags to malfunction, leading to potential safety risks, including unintentional deployment or failure to deploy in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Malfunction alerts for driver and passenger airbags
airbag sensors failure
rusted screws
liquid residue in the cup holder
and airbag system failure.
